We are currently auditing page access via the AccessLogFilter (as described on How to audit Confluence - enabling user access logging: http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/How+to+audit+Confluence+-+enabling+user+access+logging).  However, when looking at the logs, it appears the logging of the urls do not show parameters.  This causes an issue when a page titled with a special character (eg & or ?) is hit.  This is because those pages use the pageId as a parameter in the url.  When those page hits are logged, they only display as .../pages/viewpage.action leaving ambiguity as to what page was hit.  

This causes the access reports to never show hits to those pages, and leaving incorrect hit counts. Logging of the parameters will allow us to determine when all pages are hit so we can have proper logging.

