Another MediaWiki feature users would like to see in Confluence.  The way the review system works on MediaWiki when a page is edited you get an email notification with a link to the difference. The link is dynamic as is will select the difference to be between last revision you saw the most recent revision at the time you click the link. There is no more email notifications until you visit the page. I.e. if someone makes a series of small changes (as is common when editing a document and saving frequently) you get one email with a link that shows all of changes. More efficient than reviewing each change individually and reduces email traffic.

