The tables in http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/The+Confluence+data+model are not up to date.

In Confluence 3.0.x we have a new table created:
{code}
create table FOLLOW_CONNECTIONS (CONNECTIONID bigint not null, FOLLOWER varchar(255) not null, FOLLOWEE varchar(255) not null, primary key (CONNECTIONID))
{code}

Might be a good idea to provide a brief summary of what tables are available in Confluence and render it in a TOC macro.

This documentation is not crucial but handy as occasionally we have people asking support for the tables available in Confluence.

I can work with you if needed.

Cheers,
Roy

